Class Summary
AbstractNode<T extends Comparable<T>,E> A base class for Node implementations, implementing the AbstractNode.getReferences() operation.
ArithmeticNode<E> A representation of an arithmetic node in the tree representing an expression, holding a left-hand value, an operator and a right-hand value.
BooleanLiteralNode<E>  
BooleanOperatorNode<E> A Node representing a combinatorial boolean operator.

ExpressionNode<T extends Comparable<T>,E> A Node wrapping around an Expression.

IntegerReferenceNode<E> The superclass of reference nodes.
PropertySelector<E>  
ReferenceNode<T,E>  
RelationalNode<T extends Comparable<T>,E> The node representing (part of) an expression that translates to a boolean value, based on two integer-type of nodes passed in.
StringNode<E> A convenience Node wrapper around Strings.

Package org.codehaus.preon.el.ast Description

Internal expression representations. Even though not meant for it, there is nothing preventing you from using these classes in your own projects.
